{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"The immersive ugliness"},{"time":4000,"text":"of our everyday environments in America"},{"time":9000,"text":"is entropy made visible."},{"time":13000,"text":"We can't overestimate the amount of despair"},{"time":17000,"text":"that we are generating with places like this."},{"time":22000,"text":"And mostly, I want to persuade you that we have to do better"},{"time":26000,"text":"if we're going to continue the project of civilization in America."},{"time":32000,"text":"By the way, this doesn't help."},{"time":35000,"text":"Nobody's having a better day down here because of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"There are a lot of ways you can describe this."},{"time":44000,"text":"You know, I like to call it \"the national automobile slum.\""},{"time":47000,"text":"You can call it suburban sprawl."},{"time":50000,"text":"I think it's appropriate to call it"},{"time":52000,"text":"the greatest misallocation of resources in the history of the world."},{"time":57000,"text":"You can call it a technosis externality clusterfuck."},{"time":62000,"text":"And it's a tremendous problem for us."},{"time":68000,"text":"The outstanding -- the salient problem about this for us"},{"time":72000,"text":"is that these are places that are not worth caring about."},{"time":75000,"text":"We're going to talk about that some more."},{"time":78000,"text":"A sense of place:"},{"time":80000,"text":"your ability to create places that are meaningful and places of quality and character"},{"time":87000,"text":"depends entirely on your ability to define space with buildings,"},{"time":92000,"text":"and to employ the vocabularies, grammars,"},{"time":96000,"text":"syntaxes, rhythms and patterns of architecture"},{"time":100000,"text":"in order to inform us who we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103000,"text":"The public realm in America has two roles:"},{"time":109000,"text":"it is the dwelling place of our civilization and our civic life,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and it is the physical manifestation of the common good."},{"time":119000,"text":"And when you degrade the public realm,"},{"time":122000,"text":"you will automatically degrade the quality of your civic life"},{"time":125000,"text":"and the character of all the enactments of your public life and communal life that take place there."},{"time":134000,"text":"The public realm comes mostly in the form of the street in America"},{"time":139000,"text":"because we don't have the 1,000-year-old cathedral plazas"},{"time":143000,"text":"and market squares of older cultures."},{"time":147000,"text":"And your ability to define space and to create places that are worth caring about"},{"time":155000,"text":"all comes from a body of culture that we call the culture of civic design."},{"time":160000,"text":"This is a body of knowledge, method, skill and principle"},{"time":165000,"text":"that we threw in the garbage after World War II"},{"time":170000,"text":"and decided we don't need that anymore; we're not going to use it."},{"time":173000,"text":"And consequently, we can see the result all around us."},{"time":178000,"text":"The public realm has to inform us not only where we are geographically,"},{"time":183000,"text":"but it has to inform us where we are in our culture."},{"time":187000,"text":"Where we've come from, what kind of people we are, and it needs to,"},{"time":192000,"text":"by doing that, it needs to afford us a glimpse to where we're going"},{"time":198000,"text":"in order to allow us to dwell in a hopeful present."},{"time":203000,"text":"And if there is one tremendous --"},{"time":205000,"text":"if there is one great catastrophe about the places that we've built,"},{"time":208000,"text":"the human environments we've made for ourselves in the last 50 years,"},{"time":212000,"text":"it is that it has deprived us of the ability to live in a hopeful present."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"The environments we are living in, more typically, are like these."},{"time":225000,"text":"You know, this happens to be the asteroid belt of architectural garbage two miles north of my town."},{"time":231000,"text":"And remember, to create a place of character and quality,"},{"time":235000,"text":"you have to be able to define space."},{"time":237000,"text":"So how is that being accomplished here?"},{"time":239000,"text":"If you stand on the apron of the Wal-Mart over here"},{"time":242000,"text":"and try to look at the Target store over here,"},{"time":244000,"text":"you can't see it because of the curvature of the Earth. (Laughter)"},{"time":250000,"text":"That's nature's way of telling you that you're doing a poor job of defining space."},{"time":256000,"text":"Consequently, these will be places that nobody wants to be in."},{"time":259000,"text":"These will be places that are not worth caring about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"We have about, you know, 38,000 places"},{"time":266000,"text":"that are not worth caring about in the United States today."},{"time":268000,"text":"When we have enough of them, we're going to have a nation that's not worth defending."},{"time":274000,"text":"And I want you to think about that when you think about"},{"time":278000,"text":"those young men and women who are over in places like Iraq,"},{"time":280000,"text":"spilling their blood in the sand,"},{"time":282000,"text":"and ask yourself, \"What is their last thought of home?\""},{"time":287000,"text":"I hope it's not the curb cut between the Chuck E. Cheese and the Target store"},{"time":291000,"text":"because that's not good enough for Americans to be spilling their blood for. (Applause)"},{"time":297000,"text":"We need better places in this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300000,"text":"Public space. This is a good public space."},{"time":302000,"text":"It's a place worth caring about. It's well defined."},{"time":305000,"text":"It is emphatically an outdoor public room."},{"time":308000,"text":"It has something that is terribly important --"},{"time":311000,"text":"it has what's called an active and permeable membrane around the edge."},{"time":314000,"text":"That's a fancy way of saying it's got shops, bars, bistros, destinations --"},{"time":319000,"text":"things go in and out of it. It's permeable."},{"time":322000,"text":"The beer goes in and out, the waitresses go in and out,"},{"time":325000,"text":"and that activates the center of this place and makes it a place that people want to hang out in."},{"time":330000,"text":"You know, in these places in other cultures,"},{"time":334000,"text":"people just go there voluntarily because they like them."},{"time":338000,"text":"We don't have to have a craft fair here to get people to come here. (Laughter)"},{"time":341000,"text":"You know, you don't have to have a Kwanzaa festival."},{"time":344000,"text":"People just go because it's pleasurable to be there."},{"time":348000,"text":"But this is how we do it in the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"Probably the most significant public space failure in America,"},{"time":355000,"text":"designed by the leading architects of the day, Harry Cobb and I.M. Pei:"},{"time":360000,"text":"Boston City Hall Plaza."},{"time":362000,"text":"A public place so dismal that the winos don't even want to go there. (Laughter)"},{"time":368000,"text":"And we can't fix it because I.M. Pei's still alive,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and every year Harvard and M.I.T. have a joint committee to repair it."},{"time":374000,"text":"And every year they fail to because they don't want to hurt I.M. Pei's feelings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"This is the other side of the building."},{"time":380000,"text":"This was the winner of an international design award in, I think, 1966, something like that."},{"time":385000,"text":"It wasn't Pei and Cobb, another firm designed this,"},{"time":388000,"text":"but there's not enough Prozac in the world to make people feel OK about going down this block."},{"time":399000,"text":"This is the back of Boston City Hall,"},{"time":401000,"text":"the most important, you know, significant civic building in Albany -- excuse me -- in Boston."},{"time":409000,"text":"And what is the message that is coming,"},{"time":411000,"text":"what are the vocabularies and grammars that are coming, from this building"},{"time":414000,"text":"and how is it informing us about who we are?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"This, in fact, would be a better building if we put mosaic portraits"},{"time":421000,"text":"of Josef Stalin, Pol Pot, Saddam Hussein,"},{"time":426000,"text":"and all the other great despots of the 20th century on the side of the building,"},{"time":429000,"text":"because then we'd honestly be saying what the building is really communicating to us."},{"time":434000,"text":"You know, that it's a despotic building;"},{"time":436000,"text":"it wants us to feel like termites. (Laughter)"},{"time":444000,"text":"This is it on a smaller scale:"},{"time":446000,"text":"the back of the civic center in my town, Saratoga Springs, New York."},{"time":450000,"text":"By the way, when I showed this slide to a group of Kiwanians in my town,"},{"time":455000,"text":"they all rose in indignation from their creamed chicken, (Laughter)"},{"time":460000,"text":"and they shouted at me and said,"},{"time":463000,"text":"\"It was raining that day when you took that picture!\""},{"time":467000,"text":"Because this was perceived to be a weather problem. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"You know, this is a building designed like a DVD player. (Laughter)"},{"time":484000,"text":"Audio jack, power supply --"},{"time":489000,"text":"and look, you know these things are important architectural jobs for firms, right?"},{"time":494000,"text":"You know, we hire firms to design these things."},{"time":496000,"text":"You can see exactly what went on, three o'clock in the morning at the design meeting."},{"time":500000,"text":"You know, eight hours before deadline,"},{"time":502000,"text":"four architects trying to get this building in on time, right?"},{"time":506000,"text":"And they're sitting there at the long boardroom table"},{"time":509000,"text":"with all the drawings, and the renderings,"},{"time":511000,"text":"and all the Chinese food caskets are lying on the table, and --"},{"time":515000,"text":"I mean, what was the conversation that was going on there? (Laughter)"},{"time":519000,"text":"Because you know what the last word was, what the last sentence was of that meeting."},{"time":524000,"text":"It was: \"Fuck it.\" (Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"That -- that is the message of this form of architecture."},{"time":537000,"text":"The message is: We don't give a fuck! We don't give a fuck."},{"time":543000,"text":"So I went back on the nicest day of the year, just to --"},{"time":546000,"text":"you know -- do some reality testing,"},{"time":548000,"text":"and in fact, he will not even go down there because (Laughter)"},{"time":552000,"text":"it's not interesting enough for his clients,"},{"time":554000,"text":"you know, the burglars, the muggers."},{"time":557000,"text":"It's not civically rich enough for them to go down there."},{"time":562000,"text":"OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564000,"text":"The pattern of Main Street USA --"},{"time":567000,"text":"in fact, this pattern of building downtown blocks, all over the world, is fairly universal."},{"time":572000,"text":"It's not that complicated:"},{"time":574000,"text":"buildings more than one story high, built out to the sidewalk edge,"},{"time":580000,"text":"so that people who are, you know, all kinds of people can get into the building."},{"time":583000,"text":"Other activities are allowed to occur upstairs,"},{"time":587000,"text":"you know, apartments, offices, and so on."},{"time":590000,"text":"You make provision for this activity called shopping on the ground floor."},{"time":594000,"text":"They haven't learned that in Monterey."},{"time":596000,"text":"If you go out to the corner right at the main intersection right in front of this conference center,"},{"time":600000,"text":"you'll see an intersection with four blank walls on every corner."},{"time":603000,"text":"It's really incredible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605000,"text":"Anyway, this is how you compose and assemble a downtown business building,"},{"time":609000,"text":"and this is what happened when in Glens Falls, New York,"},{"time":612000,"text":"when we tried to do it again, where it was missing, right?"},{"time":614000,"text":"So the first thing they do is they pop up the retail a half a story above grade to make it sporty."},{"time":620000,"text":"OK. That completely destroys the relationship between the business and the sidewalk,"},{"time":626000,"text":"where the theoretical pedestrians are. (Laughter)"},{"time":629000,"text":"Of course, they'll never be there, as long as this is in that condition."},{"time":633000,"text":"Then because the relationship between the retail is destroyed,"},{"time":637000,"text":"we pop a handicapped ramp on that,"},{"time":640000,"text":"and then to make ourselves feel better, we put a nature Band-Aid in front of it."},{"time":644000,"text":"And that's how we do it."},{"time":646000,"text":"I call them \"nature Band-Aids\" because there's a general idea in America"},{"time":650000,"text":"that the remedy for mutilated urbanism is nature."},{"time":655000,"text":"And in fact, the remedy for wounded and mutilated urbanism is good urbanism, good buildings."},{"time":662000,"text":"Not just flower beds, not just cartoons of the Sierra Nevada Mountains."},{"time":668000,"text":"You know, that's not good enough."},{"time":669000,"text":"We have to do good buildings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671000,"text":"The street trees have really four jobs to do and that's it:"},{"time":674000,"text":"To spatially denote the pedestrian realm,"},{"time":677000,"text":"to protect the pedestrians from the vehicles in the carriageway,"},{"time":682000,"text":"to filter the sunlight onto the sidewalk,"},{"time":685000,"text":"and to soften the hardscape of the buildings"},{"time":687000,"text":"and to create a ceiling -- a vaulted ceiling -- over the street, at its best."},{"time":691000,"text":"And that's it. Those are the four jobs of the street trees."},{"time":695000,"text":"They're not supposed to be a cartoon of the North Woods;"},{"time":698000,"text":"they're not supposed to be a set for \"The Last of the Mohicans.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":703000,"text":"You know, one of the problems with the fiasco of suburbia is that it destroyed our understanding"},{"time":711000,"text":"of the distinction between the country and the town, between the urban and the rural."},{"time":715000,"text":"They're not the same thing."},{"time":717000,"text":"And we're not going to cure the problems of the urban by dragging the country into the city,"},{"time":721000,"text":"which is what a lot of us are trying to do all the time."},{"time":723000,"text":"Here you see it on a small scale -- the mothership has landed,"},{"time":727000,"text":"R2-D2 and C-3PO have stepped out to test the bark mulch"},{"time":733000,"text":"to see if they can inhabit this planet. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"A lot of this comes from the fact that the industrial city in America was such a trauma"},{"time":743000,"text":"that we developed this tremendous aversion for the whole idea of the city,"},{"time":747000,"text":"city life, and everything connected with it."},{"time":749000,"text":"And so what you see fairly early, in the mid-19th century,"},{"time":754000,"text":"is this idea that we now have to have an antidote to the industrial city,"},{"time":758000,"text":"which is going to be life in the country for everybody."},{"time":761000,"text":"And that starts to be delivered in the form of the railroad suburb:"},{"time":765000,"text":"the country villa along the railroad line,"},{"time":768000,"text":"which allows people to enjoy the amenity of the city,"},{"time":771000,"text":"but to return to the countryside every night."},{"time":773000,"text":"And believe me, there were no Wal-Marts or convenience stores out there then,"},{"time":776000,"text":"so it really was a form of country living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778000,"text":"But what happens is, of course, it mutates over the next 80 years"},{"time":782000,"text":"and it turns into something rather insidious."},{"time":784000,"text":"It becomes a cartoon of a country house, in a cartoon of the country."},{"time":789000,"text":"And that's the great non-articulated agony of suburbia"},{"time":794000,"text":"and one of the reasons that it lends itself to ridicule."},{"time":796000,"text":"Because it hasn't delivered what it's been promising for half a century now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801000,"text":"And these are typically the kind of dwellings we find there, you know."},{"time":805000,"text":"Basically, a house with nothing on the side"},{"time":808000,"text":"because this house wants to state, emphatically,"},{"time":810000,"text":"\"I'm a little cabin in the woods. There's nothing on either side of me."},{"time":813000,"text":"I don't have any eyes on the side of my head. I can't see.\""},{"time":817000,"text":"So you have this one last facade of the house,"},{"time":819000,"text":"the front, which is really a cartoon of a facade of a house."},{"time":822000,"text":"Because -- notice the porch here."},{"time":824000,"text":"Unless the people that live here are Munchkins, nobody's going to be using that."},{"time":831000,"text":"This is really, in fact, a television broadcasting a show 24/7 called \"We're Normal.\""},{"time":837000,"text":"We're normal, we're normal, we're normal, we're normal, we're normal."},{"time":840000,"text":"Please respect us, we're normal, we're normal, we're normal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842000,"text":"But we know what's going on in these houses, you know."},{"time":844000,"text":"We know that little Skippy is loading his Uzi down here,"},{"time":848000,"text":"getting ready for homeroom. (Laughter)"},{"time":852000,"text":"We know that Heather, his sister Heather, 14 years old,"},{"time":855000,"text":"is turning tricks up here to support her drug habit."},{"time":858000,"text":"Because these places, these habitats,"},{"time":861000,"text":"are inducing immense amounts of anxiety and depression in children,"},{"time":866000,"text":"and they don't have a lot of experience with medication."},{"time":870000,"text":"So they take the first one that comes along, often."},{"time":872000,"text":"These are not good enough for Americans."},{"time":874000,"text":"These are the schools we are sending them to:"},{"time":877000,"text":"The Hannibal Lecter Central School, Las Vegas, Nevada."},{"time":883000,"text":"This is a real school!"},{"time":885000,"text":"You know, but there's obviously a notion that if you let the inmates of this thing out,"},{"time":889000,"text":"that they would snatch a motorist off the street and eat his liver."},{"time":893000,"text":"So every effort is made to keep them within the building."},{"time":898000,"text":"Notice that nature is present. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":905000,"text":"We're going to have to change this behavior whether we like it or not."},{"time":907000,"text":"We are entering an epochal period of change in the world, and -- certainly in America"},{"time":912000,"text":"-- the period that will be characterized by the end of the cheap oil era."},{"time":917000,"text":"It is going to change absolutely everything."},{"time":921000,"text":"Chris asked me not to go on too long about this, and I won't,"},{"time":924000,"text":"except to say there's not going to be a hydrogen economy."},{"time":927000,"text":"Forget it. It's not going to happen."},{"time":929000,"text":"We're going to have to do something else instead."},{"time":931000,"text":"We're going to have to down-scale, re-scale, and re-size"},{"time":936000,"text":"virtually everything we do in this country and we can't start soon enough to do it."},{"time":940000,"text":"We're going to have -- (Applause) -- we're going to have to live closer to where we work."},{"time":944000,"text":"We're going to have to live closer to each other."},{"time":946000,"text":"We're going have to grow more food closer to where we live."},{"time":950000,"text":"The age of the 3,000 mile Caesar salad is coming to an end."},{"time":955000,"text":"We're going to have to -- we have a railroad system that the Bulgarians would be ashamed of!"},{"time":960000,"text":"We gotta do better than that!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":962000,"text":"And we should have started two days before yesterday."},{"time":965000,"text":"We are fortunate that the new urbanists were there, for the last 10 years,"},{"time":970000,"text":"excavating all that information that was thrown in the garbage"},{"time":974000,"text":"by our parents' generation after World War II."},{"time":977000,"text":"Because we're going to need it if we're going to learn how to reconstruct towns."},{"time":979000,"text":"We're going to need to get back this body of methodology and principle and skill"},{"time":985000,"text":"in order to re-learn how to compose meaningful places, places that are integral,"},{"time":991000,"text":"that allow -- that are living organisms in the sense that they contain all the organs of our civic life"},{"time":998000,"text":"and our communal life, deployed in an integral fashion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1003000,"text":"So that, you know, the residences make sense"},{"time":1006000,"text":"deployed in relation to the places of business, of culture and of governance."},{"time":1011000,"text":"We're going to have to re-learn what the building blocks of these things are:"},{"time":1015000,"text":"the street, the block, how to compose public space that's both large and small,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"the courtyard, the civic square"},{"time":1024000,"text":"and how to really make use of this property."},{"time":1027000,"text":"We can see some of the first ideas"},{"time":1030000,"text":"for retro-fitting some of the catastrophic property that we have in America."},{"time":1035000,"text":"The dead malls: what are we going to do with them?"},{"time":1038000,"text":"Well, in point of fact, most of them are not going to make it."},{"time":1040000,"text":"They're not going to be retro-fitted;"},{"time":1042000,"text":"they're going to be the salvage yards of the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044000,"text":"Some of them we're going to fix, though."},{"time":1046000,"text":"And we're going to fix them by imposing back on them street and block systems"},{"time":1050000,"text":"and returning to the building lot as the normal increment of development."},{"time":1056000,"text":"And if we're lucky, the result will be revivified town centers and neighborhood centers"},{"time":1062000,"text":"in our existing towns and cities."},{"time":1064000,"text":"And by the way, our towns and cities are where they are, and grew where they were"},{"time":1069000,"text":"because they occupy all the important sites."},{"time":1071000,"text":"And most of them are still going to be there,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"although the scale of them is probably going to be diminished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079000,"text":"We've got a lot of work to do."},{"time":1081000,"text":"We're not going to be rescued by the hyper-car; we're not going to be rescued by alternative fuels."},{"time":1086000,"text":"No amount or combination of alternative fuels"},{"time":1089000,"text":"is going to allow us to continue running what we're running, the way we're running it."},{"time":1093000,"text":"We're going to have to do everything very differently."},{"time":1096000,"text":"And America's not prepared."},{"time":1098000,"text":"We are sleepwalking into the future."},{"time":1101000,"text":"We're not ready for what's coming at us."},{"time":1104000,"text":"So I urge you all to do what you can."},{"time":1107000,"text":"Life in the mid-21st century is going to be about living locally."},{"time":1114000,"text":"Be prepared to be good neighbors."},{"time":1117000,"text":"Be prepared to find vocations that make you useful"},{"time":1122000,"text":"to your neighbors and to your fellow citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124000,"text":"One final thing -- I've been very disturbed about this for years,"},{"time":1127000,"text":"but I think it's particularly important for this audience."},{"time":1130000,"text":"Please, please, stop referring to yourselves as \"consumers.\" OK?"},{"time":1136000,"text":"Consumers are different than citizens."},{"time":1138000,"text":"Consumers do not have obligations, responsibilities and duties"},{"time":1143000,"text":"to their fellow human beings."},{"time":1145000,"text":"And as long as you're using that word consumer in the public discussion,"},{"time":1148000,"text":"you will be degrading the quality of the discussion we're having."},{"time":1152000,"text":"And we're going to continue being clueless"},{"time":1155000,"text":"going into this very difficult future that we face."},{"time":1158000,"text":"So thank you very much."},{"time":1159000,"text":"Please go out and do what you can to make this a land full of places that are worth caring about"},{"time":1165000,"text":"and a nation that will be worth defending. (Applause)"}]}]}